    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** headlining the roster as our definitive top play. With an elite efficiency score of 83.29, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from an ideal leadoff spot and a favorable matchup against Bello, whose 4.55 xERA presents a prime opportunity to drive up our R and HR counts. **Kyle Tucker** (73.60) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (69.24) follow as essential anchors; both capitalize on solid batting order placement and favorable park factors to remain strong daily starters. Meanwhile, **Nasim Nunez** earns a spotlight start with a 62.48 score, driven largely by the high-upside matchup against Hudson, and his defensive versatility in the middle infield\u2014combined with the premium placed on speed in our league\u2014makes him a high-efficiency asset today.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Nolan Schanuel**, whose score of 56.02 was squeezed out of the starting nine by the high-scoring floor of **Dominic Smith** and **Andy Pages**. While **Nolan Schanuel** offers a stable profile, the optimizer opted for **Andy Pages** due to a more aggressive offensive ceiling in his matchup against Taillon. We also continue to monitor the status of **Marcell Ozuna**, who remains benched with a sub-50 score (43.46) primarily due to a challenging clash with the elite arm of Woodruff (2.90 xERA). Though our depth remains strong, we are managing game caps carefully; players like **Brady House** and **Miguel Vargas** remain ready to pivot should any late lineup changes or weather disruptions arise, though for now, we are comfortable letting them rest to preserve our season-long utility.",
